No need to make cooking Quinoa that complicated. Just boil it until it is tender. To make this healthier just use olive oil instead of butter and vegetable oil and skip the sugar.

Rating: 4
This is one of my favorite go-to recipes. I serve it as a side dish or a salad, and often take it to potlucks as I think it's good at room temperature, and it doesn't need heating or refrigeration. Steaming the quinoa really does make a difference, and it's really not much of a hassle. I do make one change though. I use 3 tablespoons (or usually a bit more) of good quality olive oil instead of the combination of butter and vegetable oil. I think it works better as a salad this way. It can stand a bit more lime juice too. I usually use the zest and juice of a lime, but this does depend on the lime of course. Halved cherry tomatoes work well instead of the diced ones for an attractive presentation.

