I love this recipe and have made it numerous times. My guests love it too and usually want the recipe. I make my quinoa in the rice cooker with the same ratios as white rice, 1 cup quinoa and 2 cups water and I omit the salt as it makes the dish way to salty. I then let it cool before adding the dressing. I usually make a double batch of quinoa and add a can of corn and some feta. I don't double the beans or the tomatoes. I also use olive oil instead of vegetable oil and I do not usually double the butter in the dressing when I double the recipe. I usually add more zest than called for as well. This recipe is one of those recipes that you can play with till your hearts content and you wouldn't mess it up...except by adding too much salt which I did the first time I made it:-)

