Rating: 3
I forgot to add, if you cook the quinoa in an electric rice cooker it comes up fluffy and this recipe is a cinch! We use 1 1/2 cups of water to every cup of quinoa. Washing it is easiest if you put the dry grains into a fine strainer/sieve, then submerge this in a bowl of water (taking care that the grains don't overflow out of the sieve into the bowl) where you can rub the grains with your fingers before draining/rinsing - if you wash it three times as specified, this should get rid of any bitter taste.

