Rating: 4
This was my first time cooking quinoa and this recipe was SO GOOD!! I loved the lime dressing so much it just left me wanting more. I have made it three times now and I used two small limes (which is about four tablespoons) and add another half teaspoon of sugar in the dressing. My sieve has a plastic handle and rim and melted the first time during the steaming step. Subsequent times I found that if I poured some of the hot liquid into a bowl that the sieve could fit in (above the liquid), and then put the bowl in the pan, the liquid was hot enough to steam the quinoa without turning on the heat. Covered with towel and lid as recommended and it came out great, fluffy. I used about a half cup of vegetable broth in my boiling water, just enough to give it a little flavor. Otherwise followed recipe and it's just delicious. My only problem is that I eat it all within the first few hours! Thanks for this great recipe. I love knowing that this dish that tastes so good is also so healthy.

