Rating: 0
Good grief, people. Could we please stop equating "less fat" with "healthier" and "fat" with "unhealthy"? Fat is not inherently unhealthy. Your body needs it. Furthermore, fat equals flavor, ask any chef. When you omit or reduce fat from a recipe, you are NOT making it "healthier" - you are making it less flavorful. And by the way, food cannot be "healthy," since it is not alive (well, not usually and not for long after you eat it, anyway). The correct word is "healthful." I'm going to make this for a Xmas Orphan lunch. I expect it to be a big hit, with all that lovely flavorful butter.

