I thought this was really bland. after making as directed, i had to keep adding ingredients just to give it some flavor, and i still found it boring. For a good quinoa recipe: saute 1 onion in olive oil till soft, add 1 crushed garlic clove and about 1/4-1/2 tsp red pepper flakes. add quinoa, saute, then add appropriate amount water and cook until water absorbed. In the meantime, chop 2-3 tomato, 1/4-1/2 cup chopped fresh mint, and 4 oz of crumbled feta. mix into cooked quinoa and season with salt and pepper. easier and better than this recipe.

